{"word":"H357 - אַיָּלֹון - ʼAyâlôwn - ah-yaw-lone' - Aijalon","slug":"H357","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אַיָּלֹון</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼAyâlôwn"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ah-yaw-lone'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Aijalon"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>איּלון</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>'ayâlôn</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>ah-yaw-lone'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Ajalon or Aijalon = \"field of deer\" <ol><li>Levitical city in Dan, 14 miles or 25 kilometers NW of Jerusalem, later ruled by the Amorites, then the Benjamites of Judah, then by the Philistines</li><li>a city of Zebulun, site unknown</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H354\">H354</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Location "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H193\">H193</a>, <a href=\"#/H195\">H195</a>, <a href=\"#/H197\">H197</a>, <a href=\"#/H198\">H198</a>, <a href=\"#/H352\">H352</a>, <a href=\"#/H354\">H354</a>, <a href=\"#/H355\">H355</a>, <a href=\"#/H356\">H356</a>, <a href=\"#/H359\">H359</a>, <a href=\"#/H361\">H361</a>, <a href=\"#/H362\">H362</a>, <a href=\"#/H364\">H364</a>, <a href=\"#/H365\">H365</a>, <a href=\"#/H424\">H424</a>, <a href=\"#/H425\">H425</a>, <a href=\"#/H436\">H436</a>, <a href=\"#/H440\">H440</a>"}]}